To customize the appearance and content of notifications, consider implementing a custom notification layout and/or behavior. This can be done using the `androidBigPicture` or `androidBigText` properties of the `firebase.notifications.Notification` object, which allow you to specify custom images or text for the notification. Additionally, you can attach custom data to the notification using the `data` property, which can be used to trigger specific actions within the app when the notification is clicked or opened.
